1
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:16,440
Sir,

2
00:00:17,330 --> 00:00:18,280
have you seen

3
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,650
an outsider with a beast-pattern tattoo?

4
00:00:19,650 --> 00:00:21,110
The tattoo is around here.

5
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,040
What's wrong with him?

6
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,170
That man is a bandit.

7
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:27,510
He abducted the Mountain God's bride

8
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,110
and committed a grave crime.

9
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:33,230
Sit down.

10
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,570
Tell me about it.

11
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,060
What exactly was going on?

12
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:42,330
Let me think whether I've seen him.

13
00:00:42,330 --> 00:00:43,790
He's just some pretty boy,

14
00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:45,790
actually quite good-looking.

15
00:00:45,860 --> 00:00:47,860
I don't buy that he's a bandit at all.

16
00:00:48,390 --> 00:00:50,320
He must be having an affair
with the bride.

17
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,030
That's why she didn't want

18
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:52,490
to marry the Mountain God.

19
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:54,300
They must've slept together—

20
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,500
two filthy bastards.

21
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:56,530
Guys like him

22
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:57,970
bring bad luck to their parents—

23
00:00:57,970 --> 00:00:59,170
born lowly and worthless.

24
00:00:59,170 --> 00:01:03,100
If we catch him, we'll castrate him
and parade him through the streets.

25
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:04,989
Is the bride beautiful?

26
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:06,140
She is.

27
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:08,190
If she's untouched,

28
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:09,460
taking her home as a concubine

29
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:10,720
wouldn't be bad at all.

30
00:01:13,150 --> 00:01:13,730
Hey man,

31
00:01:14,010 --> 00:01:15,780
where did you come from outside?

32
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:17,140
Where I come from—

33
00:01:17,930 --> 00:01:19,120
what's it to you?

34
00:01:23,130 --> 00:01:24,230
Just asking.

35
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,180
Just asking.

36
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,000
Casual chat.

37
00:01:26,030 --> 00:01:26,890
What about you?

38
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:28,610
Local?

39
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,020
Got a daughter?

40
00:01:33,690 --> 00:01:34,690
I have a daughter.

41
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:37,789
How old is she?

42
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,570
Has she reached marriageable age?

43
00:01:41,979 --> 00:01:44,410
About the right age to get married.

44
00:01:45,330 --> 00:01:47,190
When your daughter gets married,

45
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:49,490
will she also take this route?

46
00:01:50,050 --> 00:01:52,310
Will she run into a bride kidnapping too?

47
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,160
What do you mean?

48
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,740
Have mercy! Please, spare me!

49
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:06,280
Am I being too harsh?

50
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,210
No, no, not at all.

51
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:07,810
Not at all.

52
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,380
Will you kill me then?

53
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,330
I wouldn't dare.

54
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:11,340
I wouldn't dare.

55
00:02:16,150 --> 00:02:18,680
Seems like I still haven't
been harsh enough.

56
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,850
I wouldn't dare do that again.

57
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:38,960
Sir, please spare me!

58
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,930
Sir, please spare me!

59
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:41,420
Sir, please spare me! Don't kill me!

60
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:42,460
Don't kill me!

61
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,210
Sir, please have mercy!
Please have mercy!

62
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:45,870
Where is the Mountain God's
wedding taking place?

63
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:46,650
Spare me!

64
00:02:47,530 --> 00:02:49,450
After you pass the mountain pass
and reach Xitou Beach,

65
00:02:49,450 --> 00:02:51,520
just follow the stream forward—

66
00:02:51,550 --> 00:02:53,350
that's the Mountain God Temple.

67
00:03:03,710 --> 00:03:04,560
Please, spare me!

68
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,560
Please, spare me!

69
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,300
Spare me.

70
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:06,750
No, no—

71
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,060
please, spare me!

72
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:12,330
Sir, please spare me!
Sir, please spare me!

73
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:13,250
Spare me, sir.

74
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,380
Spare me, sir.

75
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,490
Don't kill me!

76
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:17,650
Spare me, sir. Spare me, sir.

77
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:18,910
Spare me, sir.

78
00:04:45,890 --> 00:04:52,280
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

79
00:04:52,570 --> 00:04:55,350
[Episode 28]

80
00:04:58,190 --> 00:05:00,720
This is the only way
into the Mountain God Temple.

81
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,950
The bridal procession

82
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:04,080
should be coming through here, right?

83
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:09,470
They're here.

84
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:14,210
Why is there no bride in this procession?

85
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:15,680
Don't tell me

86
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:17,130
that after what happened
between me and the bride earlier,

87
00:05:17,130 --> 00:05:18,690
they've hidden her away.

88
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,850
Right now, the top priority

89
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,770
is finding the bride.

90
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:29,930
Let's go down and blend into the crowd

91
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:31,260
and ask someone around.

92
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,409
Help me!

93
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,260
[Wulang Huazha, Local of Nanqiang]

94
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:34,140
Help me!

95
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:41,110
Quick, say you've caught the man
who abducted the mountain bride!

96
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,970
I-I caught the man
who abducted the mountain bride!

97
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,920
Do they not understand what you're saying?

98
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:52,100
I said I've caught the man
who abducted the mountain bride—

99
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:52,870
it's him!

100
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,680
Ask who their leader is.

101
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:56,770
Ask for a reward from them.

102
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:58,170
I want to see your leader.

103
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,760
Is there a reward for this?

104
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,450
This is the man who abducted the bride.

105
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:09,860
Yes, he is.

106
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:10,920
He's a beggar from the mountains.

107
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,260
Who are you calling a beggar?

108
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:14,120
I'm a Daoist priest,
a legitimate cultivator.

109
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:14,860
Tell them

110
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:16,270
you were the bodyguard
I hired before,

111
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:18,130
-To fulfill your duty...
-I... I...

112
00:06:18,130 --> 00:06:18,450
And then later you realized...

113
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:18,890
I'm the bodyguard.

114
00:06:18,890 --> 00:06:20,800
-You got angry and caught me...
-He didn't pay me.

115
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,190
So I arrested him.

116
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:22,540
Do you think I'm deaf?

117
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:25,810
Cut their hamstrings.

118
00:06:26,450 --> 00:06:29,040
Take them back
and leave them to the bride's families.

119
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,180
Invoke the Patriarch!

120
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:33,580
Five-fire orthodox law—
thunder spirit, ignite the flames!

121
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,440
That's incredible!

122
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,800
This guy can use sorcery!

123
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,159
Zhang Qianjun,

124
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:50,890
let's get out of here!

125
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,700
We'll meet again!

126
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,110
Boss, he got away!

127
00:06:59,740 --> 00:07:00,720
Sorcerer,

128
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:03,600
are you just going to
abandon your companion like that?

129
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,680
Actually, that little Taoist just now

130
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,830
was just handling logistics.

131
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:07,630
I'm the real professional here.

132
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,170
Nobody move!

133
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,070
Sir,

134
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,400
we're just

135
00:07:14,870 --> 00:07:15,890
hired to do a job

136
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:17,100
and earn a living.

137
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:24,720
See? All thanks to me.

138
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:29,400
Damn it!

139
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:32,510
What?

140
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,130
Yueshu is gone.

141
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:36,790
You really don't know
where the bride is hidden?

142
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:38,430
To be honest,

143
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:40,860
I grew up with this bride
since we were kids.

144
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:42,990
Bailejing hasn't been peaceful lately—

145
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:44,050
there've been rumors

146
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:45,909
that something in the forest
has been eating people.

147
00:07:45,909 --> 00:07:47,110
I came along this time

148
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,640
to protect Yueshu.

149
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:51,580
And you managed to lose her?

150
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,960
The procession is so long

151
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,720
that those in front thought
she was behind,

152
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,830
and those behind
thought she was in front.

153
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:58,030
If it weren't for you,

154
00:07:58,170 --> 00:07:59,690
we might not have
even noticed

155
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:00,680
Yueshu was missing

156
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,940
until we reached the Feikun Balu Temple.

157
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,430
Did you see two men—

158
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,570
one a Taoist,

159
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,810
and the other a pretty boy?

160
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:08,430
What?

161
00:08:08,580 --> 00:08:09,250
I'm asking you—

162
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,770
have you seen two men?

163
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,520
What's going on, sir?

164
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,100
And where are the other group of men?

165
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,130
The ones who were chasing me just now.

166
00:08:16,130 --> 00:08:18,130
I didn't see them in the procession.

167
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:19,230
Follow me.

168
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:23,200
The best way to hide someone

169
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,460
isn't to conceal them in a crowd—

170
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:28,720
but beneath lanterns
and the roar of drums.

171
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:29,730
Found them.

172
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:48,010
Then why is there
still another procession?

173
00:08:52,690 --> 00:08:53,890
Wait here for me.

174
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,040
Don't be afraid.

175
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,170
I'm here to save you.

176
00:09:26,770 --> 00:09:27,550
Mentor.

177
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:29,600
Why is it you?

178
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:31,330
Where's the bride?

179
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:33,260
She was switched. Can't you tell?

180
00:09:33,260 --> 00:09:35,750
Do I really have to wait for you
to do everything?

181
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,250
I'm the bride now.

182
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,860
Get down, now.

183
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,780
You're such a liability—

184
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:42,240
how am I supposed to get married
with you in tow?

185
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,100
Should I go too?

186
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,300
Stay hidden.

187
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:47,860
I'll handle things here.
Wait for my signal.

188
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:48,500
Alright.

189
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:49,340
I'm going.

190
00:09:57,650 --> 00:09:58,710
What's going on?

191
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,880
What do you mean what's going on?

192
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,080
That's my mentor.

193
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,900
Some things are as inevitable as rain
or a mentor wanting to marry—

194
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:07,700
just let it be.

195
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,360
But that escort procession
is definitely suspicious.

196
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,440
Those boxes are covered in talismans.

197
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,600
They don't look like they're
meant for the living at all.

198
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,610
Who would send off a living bride
with talismans all over?

199
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:19,670
What about Yueshu?

200
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,480
Could she be in danger?

201
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:23,320
You care about her that much?

202
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,250
You've still got feelings for her?

203
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:26,150
No, no.

204
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,320
We just grew up together.

205
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,530
Well, this bride sure is quite the flirt—

206
00:10:32,530 --> 00:10:34,370
she's got the chief, and she's still
fooling around with other people.

207
00:10:34,370 --> 00:10:35,570
Don't talk nonsense.

208
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:37,260
Yueshu is a good girl.

209
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,570
If it weren't for her sick father
and younger brother,

210
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:42,770
she wouldn't still be unmarried by now.

211
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:44,820
Well, if you're that close with her,

212
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,330
do you know our chief?

213
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:47,840
Your chief?

214
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,490
He has a tattoo on his chest,
something like this.

215
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:04,310
I've been blind to the truth—

216
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:06,060
with skills like yours,

217
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:07,200
I should've known

218
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:09,160
you're one of Feikun Balu's people.

219
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,540
So if he really is some kind of deity,

220
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:11,710
do you have a place here

221
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:13,570
where Feikun Balu is worshipped?

222
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:15,460
Yes, there are temples. Many temples.

223
00:11:15,460 --> 00:11:16,270
Feikun Balu Temple?

224
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,130
Yes, yes.

225
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,210
So would the bridal procession

226
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:22,250
be heading to the Feikun Balu Temple?

227
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:22,860
Yes.

228
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:25,840
The bride will be sent
to the Feikun Balu Temple in Xigudong,

229
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,860
where the priest
will preside over the wedding.

230
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:29,290
The bridal procession won't stay—

231
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:30,840
they'll continue on to Xigudong
for the Bone-Washing Ceremony.

232
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,640
And the bride?

233
00:11:32,820 --> 00:11:33,870
The priest says

234
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,310
the bride will remain
in the Feikun Balu Temple

235
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:37,680
and serve the Mountain God.

236
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,410
That is the honor of Bailejing.

237
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:41,470
I thought the Zhang family was finished.

238
00:11:41,470 --> 00:11:42,330
I didn't expect

239
00:11:42,890 --> 00:11:44,940
the Zhang family
to still have a temple here.

240
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:46,590
This chief is something.

241
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:49,420
I hope he can save Mentor and Shrimpie.

242
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,230
I've got an idea—follow me.

243
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:09,210
Zhang Hailou,
don't say I'm not a loyal brother—

244
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:10,340
I'm here to help you.

245
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:58,140
Don't worry.

246
00:12:58,640 --> 00:13:00,610
It's just part of the ritual.

247
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:03,210
[Su Li, High Priest of Bailejing]

248
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:03,710
Feikun Balu will protect you.

249
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,030
High Priest,

250
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,450
what are

251
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,930
these corpses

252
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:11,840
being dug up for?

253
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,340
To offer them to Feikun Balu.

254
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:17,620
So you're saying I'm supposed
to be married off to Feikun Balu?

255
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:18,860
What exactly

256
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:20,770
is Feikun Balu?

257
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,390
You'll see soon enough.

258
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:24,340
Remember—

259
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:26,730
when serving him,

260
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:28,250
don't look him in the eye,

261
00:13:29,070 --> 00:13:31,950
unless you want to anger him.

262
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:39,990
Now,

263
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:42,890
is everything here
being done as a bridal ritual?

264
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,180
Yes, High Priest.

265
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:46,150
All we have to do is deliver
the bride and these corpses

266
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:47,620
to the Feikun Balu Temple

267
00:13:47,650 --> 00:13:49,780
as offerings to the great Feikun Balu.

268
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:08,220
Sir,

269
00:14:08,970 --> 00:14:09,830
what is this...

270
00:14:09,930 --> 00:14:10,860
No way like this.

271
00:14:10,930 --> 00:14:12,340
This shadow procession is too sinister.

272
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:14,280
I need to get in there
to be with my mentor.

273
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,370
With your build,

274
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,640
you can just go in as a porter.

275
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:25,610
I literally just
came through here, didn't I?

276
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:28,250
Oh, Zhang Qianjun...

277
00:14:28,490 --> 00:14:30,220
You can even get lost like this?

278
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:32,430
How useless can you be?

279
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,630
Feng Huang?

280
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,040
What are you doing lying there?

281
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:53,100
Don't come over!

282
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,220
Huh?

283
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,460
Don't come over!

284
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,220
Why do my legs feel so weak
all of a sudden?

285
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:03,890
You idiot—

286
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:05,910
what are you even good for?

287
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,970
That's Nanqiang Horse-Stinger Grass.

288
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,980
It's poisonous.

289
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:11,990
How was I supposed to know?

290
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:14,730
Is anyone there?

291
00:15:28,830 --> 00:15:29,970
Give me your hand.

292
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:41,770
Are you stupid?

293
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,530
If this grass is highly poisonous,

294
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,800
you'd still come save me?

295
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,120
Then why didn't you tell me earlier?

296
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:53,410
Have you been staying
in the Taoist temple for too long?

297
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,430
If I weren't kind-hearted,

298
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,460
you'd already be dead.

299
00:15:58,410 --> 00:15:59,740
I attempted to save you—

300
00:16:00,010 --> 00:16:01,220
what did I do wrong?

301
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:03,970
You're so capable,

302
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:05,440
then tell me—

303
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,810
what are we supposed to do now?

304
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:10,270
Well, since you came to my rescue,

305
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:13,530
let's head over and meet up
with my sister first.

306
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:14,060
Let's go.

307
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,100
You're okay now?

308
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,500
I'm fine.

309
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,270
People from the Zhang family

310
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:24,580
are all in good health.

311
00:16:29,540 --> 00:16:30,860
Just like that?

312
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:31,820
Let me help you.

313
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,110
Are you sure about this—

314
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:57,760
going for revenge?

315
00:17:02,030 --> 00:17:03,160
I've made up my mind.

316
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:05,190
I'm going to get revenge.

317
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:07,060
Don't try to talk me out of it.

318
00:17:07,569 --> 00:17:08,700
I'm not going to try.

319
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,200
And I can't really understand
what you're going through,

320
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,609
so I don't have the right

321
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,740
to stop you either.

322
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:20,839
Little Taoist,

323
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,849
what happened—no more preaching?

324
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:23,950
Did that toxic weed

325
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,700
cure your yapping?

326
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:30,160
I've spent my whole life
in the mountains,

327
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,450
guarding a Taoist temple

328
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,510
and a firework.

329
00:17:36,670 --> 00:17:38,530
I never had the chance to go out,

330
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,660
to see what the outside world

331
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:41,590
is really like.

332
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,780
But honestly...
I've always wanted to see it.

333
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:47,280
I want to come down the mountain,

334
00:17:48,530 --> 00:17:49,700
see the world,

335
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:52,550
and find a firework

336
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:54,420
that belongs to me.

337
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:00,640
Sounds good.

338
00:18:01,970 --> 00:18:03,540
You go find your firework,

339
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,530
I'll go take my revenge.

340
00:18:06,570 --> 00:18:07,770
If I die,

341
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:11,450
just set off a firework for me—

342
00:18:12,010 --> 00:18:12,910
count it

343
00:18:13,290 --> 00:18:14,490
as visiting my grave.

344
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:20,090
What's with the "mm-hmm"?

345
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:21,900
Have you forgotten how to talk again?

346
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:25,300
Why don't you go roll around
in that grass a couple more times?

347
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:28,320
How are you feeling now? Let me help you.

348
00:18:49,910 --> 00:18:59,710
[Feikun Palu Temple]

349
00:19:05,130 --> 00:19:17,490
[Feikun Palu Temple]

350
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:22,140
The auspicious hour is approaching.

351
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:23,870
Prepare the wedding ceremony.

352
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:26,590
Don't keep Feikun Balu waiting too long.

353
00:19:29,550 --> 00:19:30,660
Soon, you will

354
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:32,900
be married to the great Feikun Balu

355
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:34,980
and fulfill your destiny.

356
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,250
Don't worry—your father
and younger brother,

357
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:37,980
I will take care of them for you.

358
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:39,720
I will take good care of them.

359
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:43,930
If she's to marry Feikun Balu,

360
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:46,010
then you're not allowed to touch her.

361
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:48,070
This is my younger sister
who comes with me as part of the dowry.

362
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:50,200
She will stand with me, no matter what.

363
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,280
The stench of corpses...

364
00:21:20,660 --> 00:21:22,060
There are drag marks...

365
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:28,190
What are you doing wandering around

366
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:30,550
instead of taking care of the bride?

367
00:22:32,530 --> 00:22:33,400
Sir,

368
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,180
I came out to find something to eat.

369
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:37,380
We can't let the bride go hungry, can we?

370
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:42,810
Sir,

371
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:45,400
my sister is supposed
to be marrying a deity, right?

372
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,990
Why is this place so eerie?

373
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:50,620
It clearly looks like she's marrying
some kind of monster.

374
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:51,750
Shh!

375
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:55,430
Come here.

376
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,800
A deity is a deity—

377
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:01,020
don't talk nonsense.

378
00:23:06,180 --> 00:23:07,100
Miss,

379
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:08,050
you

380
00:23:08,050 --> 00:23:09,380
don't need to be afraid.

381
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,350
When the wedding ceremony starts,

382
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:13,350
only your sister will be allowed in.

383
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,890
Even if you want to,
you won't be allowed to enter.

384
00:23:15,890 --> 00:23:16,890
Just stay quietly

385
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:19,610
in the room and wait.

386
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:21,890
I'll make sure you...

387
00:23:34,390 --> 00:23:36,270
How did this thing end up here?

388
00:23:36,770 --> 00:23:38,970
Could everything be connected to this?

389
00:23:43,730 --> 00:23:45,690
Sir, come on, let me help you up.

390
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:49,900
Sir,

391
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:52,230
I see you're close with the High Priest.

392
00:23:52,380 --> 00:23:53,520
Tell me a bit more please.

393
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:54,780
Let me learn a bit.

394
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:56,780
What exactly is going on with
the mountain bride ritual

395
00:23:56,780 --> 00:23:58,190
in Bailejing?

396
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,220
So you're saying

397
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:11,070
Bailejing's so-called
"marrying the mountain bride"

398
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:13,000
is actually a sacrificial ritual?

399
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:15,620
And it's not the first time either.

400
00:24:16,530 --> 00:24:19,130
I found this in a crack
in the main hall doorway—

401
00:24:19,610 --> 00:24:20,870
Wanduo's fingernail.

402
00:24:23,070 --> 00:24:24,150
I looked into it.

403
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:27,550
A few months ago,

404
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:28,770
a major disaster broke out
deep in Nanqiang.

405
00:24:28,770 --> 00:24:31,510
Strange mist spread everywhere,
and many people died.

406
00:24:31,510 --> 00:24:33,420
The roads between
the six mountain settlements

407
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:34,530
were completely cut off.

408
00:24:34,530 --> 00:24:35,550
Priest Su Ya

409
00:24:35,830 --> 00:24:36,980
then publicly claimed

410
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:40,160
that someone had violated tribal taboos,

411
00:24:40,660 --> 00:24:42,240
triggering the catastrophe—

412
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,550
and that things were still getting worse.

413
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:44,700
Priest Su Ya,

414
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:47,070
to prevent panic
from spreading through Bailejing,

415
00:24:47,070 --> 00:24:48,960
came up with this idea
of marrying the mountain bride.

416
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:49,770
On the surface,

417
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:51,500
it's meant to calm the people.

418
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,740
In reality, it's used to cover up

419
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:54,960
disappearances and deaths,

420
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,010
and stop anyone
from investigating further.

421
00:24:58,290 --> 00:25:00,090
But one thing I can't figure out—

422
00:25:00,410 --> 00:25:02,210
why do they need so many corpses?

423
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,380
Also, this thing

424
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:07,680
and Mo Yungao

425
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:09,660
have both suddenly appeared
in Nanqiang recently.

426
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:10,680
Do you think this change

427
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:13,210
has something to do
with Mo Yungao's arrival?

428
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,020
My head hurts.

429
00:25:14,330 --> 00:25:15,590
I'm not the Director—

430
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,420
why should I care?

431
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:18,080
That's for you to think about.

432
00:25:23,610 --> 00:25:26,010
Right—so I'm the Director now, huh?

433
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:31,540
Then of course
we'll turn their plan against them.

434
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:35,310
Wait—what are you so worked up about?

435
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:37,250
The last bride died such a horrible death.

436
00:25:37,250 --> 00:25:38,250
What, not pretty?

437
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,660
You look drop-dead gorgeous.

438
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:48,290
What happened to the original bride?

439
00:25:48,290 --> 00:25:49,750
She was already released.

440
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,870
Nobody's going to stop my wedding—

441
00:25:52,180 --> 00:25:53,780
come on, help me get dressed.

442
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,560
Yueshu, wait for me here for a moment.

443
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:27,810
Move!

444
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:22,580
Haiqi!

445
00:28:23,250 --> 00:28:24,680
I'm serious about you—

446
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:26,580
come out and see me!

447
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:27,880
Haiqi!

448
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,920
I'm serious about you!

449
00:28:31,350 --> 00:28:32,140
Haiqi!

450
00:28:32,870 --> 00:28:34,530
Why are you looking for my mom?

451
00:28:35,770 --> 00:28:37,550
My dad isn't home today.

452
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:39,500
Why don't you stay for a meal?

453
00:28:41,180 --> 00:28:42,640
Don't joke around.

454
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,660
Miss Zhang isn't that kind of woman.

455
00:28:45,050 --> 00:28:46,720
You know what kind of woman

456
00:28:46,750 --> 00:28:48,090
she is better than anyone, huh?

457
00:28:48,090 --> 00:28:49,510
Flowers and gifts—

458
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:51,030
we'll accept those.

459
00:28:51,250 --> 00:28:51,850
No.

460
00:28:51,990 --> 00:28:53,180
But as for seeing her in person,
that won't be necessary.

461
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:54,550
I haven't even seen her yet.

462
00:28:54,550 --> 00:28:55,370
Go back.

463
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:56,250
Go on, leave.

464
00:28:56,570 --> 00:28:57,440
How can you treat me like this?

465
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,570
We won't see you out.

466
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:00,710
Young Master, what do we do?

467
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:02,180
What do you mean what do we do?

468
00:29:02,180 --> 00:29:02,710
Let's go.

469
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:04,140
Goodbye.

470
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:11,660
Mentor,

471
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:14,070
this is already the third one today.

472
00:29:14,070 --> 00:29:15,220
Aren't you tired of it?
I'm getting sick of it.

473
00:29:15,220 --> 00:29:17,080
Why don't you just marry someone?

474
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:19,530
Are you stupid?

475
00:29:20,010 --> 00:29:21,030
If she gets married,

476
00:29:21,030 --> 00:29:22,120
what happens to us?

477
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:23,040
You're the stupid one.

478
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:25,500
We'd just follow her
after she gets married.

479
00:29:27,530 --> 00:29:29,330
I'd rather live freely on my own.

480
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,800
What do I need a man for?

481
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:32,760
Besides,

482
00:29:33,380 --> 00:29:36,580
don't I already have you two
to take care of me in my old age?

483
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:44,930
What are you looking at?

484
00:29:50,290 --> 00:29:52,620
I'm looking at how beautiful my mentor is.

485
00:29:57,020 --> 00:29:57,740
No,

486
00:29:58,720 --> 00:29:59,920
I don't like this one.

487
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:02,800
I think the previous outfit looked better.

488
00:30:02,900 --> 00:30:04,100
This one looks great.

489
00:30:04,790 --> 00:30:05,690
I'm going to change.

490
00:30:05,690 --> 00:30:06,620
You go out first.

491
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,380
But if I go out dressed like this,

492
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:10,580
won't I blow my cover?

493
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:13,330
Then find an empty latrine and hide in it.

494
00:30:16,270 --> 00:30:16,880
Fine.

495
00:30:17,490 --> 00:30:18,400
Just hurry up—

496
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:20,080
don't keep everyone waiting.

497
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:22,450
High Priest,

498
00:31:22,530 --> 00:31:24,310
after every ritual is completed,

499
00:31:24,310 --> 00:31:25,740
before Feikun Balu descends,

500
00:31:25,740 --> 00:31:27,270
Priest Su Ya  always leaves from here.

501
00:31:27,270 --> 00:31:29,060
What is this place inside?

502
00:31:29,270 --> 00:31:32,260
It seems to be a structure built
by people from a long time ago.

503
00:31:32,260 --> 00:31:34,460
Each time, Priest Su Ya goes deep inside

504
00:31:34,670 --> 00:31:36,050
and takes something before leaving.

505
00:31:36,050 --> 00:31:36,870
Could it be...

506
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:39,570
the secret of Feikun Balu

507
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:41,550
is hidden in here?

508
00:31:42,220 --> 00:31:44,240
High Priest,
the auspicious hour has arrived.

509
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:44,830
Let's go.

510
00:33:35,860 --> 00:33:36,450
Mentor.

511
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:40,400
Mentor.

512
00:33:42,810 --> 00:33:43,590
Hurry up—

513
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,650
are you done yet? I'm coming in.

514
00:33:57,970 --> 00:33:59,960
You're running away at a time like this?

515
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:00,700
Seriously?

516
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,350
Bride,

517
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,350
hurry up.

518
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,350
Are you ready yet?

519
00:34:09,969 --> 00:34:11,170
Come on—are you done?

520
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:13,030
Why are you rushing me

521
00:34:13,030 --> 00:34:14,060
so much?

522
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:16,050
Are you in a hurry
to be reborn or something?

523
00:34:16,050 --> 00:34:17,710
Let's go. Time to get married.

524
00:37:42,820 --> 00:37:44,080
It's the Zhang family.

525
00:37:45,770 --> 00:37:48,440
So the source of the resurrection drug
really is Nanqiang—

526
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,040
and it comes
from the Zhang family themselves.

527
00:37:52,830 --> 00:37:56,560
They were trying to use this medicine
to bring the dead back to life.

528
00:38:00,150 --> 00:38:02,110
But how could the Zhang family

529
00:38:02,110 --> 00:38:04,840
develop something like this
in a place like this?

530
00:38:05,510 --> 00:38:07,770
What exactly is hidden deep in Nanqiang?

531
00:38:17,010 --> 00:38:18,940
They actually came back to life...

532
00:38:20,660 --> 00:38:22,320
But these resurrected people

533
00:38:22,690 --> 00:38:24,260
don't seem normal.

534
00:38:25,110 --> 00:38:28,310
These deranged people
took another dose of the medicine,

535
00:38:28,530 --> 00:38:30,380
and they seem to have returned to normal.

536
00:38:30,380 --> 00:38:31,510
If that's the case,

537
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:36,300
there must be something here
that can restore people to normal.

538
00:38:36,300 --> 00:38:37,820
Where is that medicine?

539
00:38:45,120 --> 00:38:45,850
These...

540
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:49,500
are the medicinal materials
used to refine that drug.

541
00:38:54,130 --> 00:38:55,230
A cliff...

542
00:39:09,590 --> 00:39:10,630
So that's it...

543
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:14,130
they use Zhang family blood
to make the medicine.

544
00:39:30,500 --> 00:39:32,560
So this is what's hidden deep inside.

545
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,550
Then Zhang Haixia might also...

